#block(width: 100%, inset: 1em)[
  #align(center)[#text(weight: "bold")[Abstract]]
   We bosonise the complex-boson realisations of the \$W\_\infty\$ and \$W\_{1+\infty}\$ algebras. We obtain nonlinear realisations of \$W\_\infty\$ and \$W\_{1+\infty}\$ in terms of a pair of fermions and a real scalar. By further bosonising the fermions, we then obtain realisations of \$W\_\infty\$ in terms of two scalars. Keeping the most non-linear terms in the scalars only, we arrive at two-scalar realisations of classical \$w\_\infty\$.
]

